# NestJS structure

- Controllers: request/response mapping only.
- Services: business logic.
- Modules: feature-based grouping.
- Repositories: data access only (queries, persistence).
- Validate inputs with DTOs and class-validator.
- Throw Nest HTTP exceptions from controllers; let services throw domain errors.
